{#- Phase O Unit 17 — Call 1.5 (self-reported p_success probe) user message.

     Rendered between Call 1 (task layer) and Call 2 (forfeit layer) when
     ``ExperimentConfig.use_psuccess_probe=True``. Its job is narrow:
     elicit the agent's own retrospective confidence that the ACTION it
     just committed to in Call 1 is correct. The primary product is the
     single scalar ``psuccess_self`` — the thinking-token cost
     (``ri_probe``) is a secondary, optional measurement (see below).

     Guardrails retained from the original Unit 17 design:
       (a) forfeit / continue reasoning suppressed so it does not leak
           into Call 2's ri_forfeit measurement;
       (b) Call 1 thinking NOT echoed so Call 1.5 thinking stays an
           independent sample (no mechanical carry-over of prior
           reasoning into ri_probe).

     ri_probe measurement policy (Unit 17.9 smoke observation,
     2026-04-22): in practice Gemini 2.5 Flash treats the probe as a
     re-derivation prompt and runs full rule-space enumeration in
     thinking (e.g. "36 of 48 consistent rules → 75%"), giving
     ri_probe ≈ 2× ri_task. This is NOT a bug for the primary analysis:
     psuccess_self is the scalar we care about, and the enumeration
     actually grounds it. The original "probe should be light"
     expectation is abandoned. ri_probe is kept in TurnResult as a
     hook for future metacognitive analyses (e.g. Δ = ri_probe −
     ri_task as "metacog above task baseline"), not as a current
     measurement gate.

     Wording policy (Phase O Unit 17.7 — implicit chaining, structural
     defense): the chaining mechanism is NOT disclosed in the prompt,
     and the Call 2 menu does NOT surface the reported value. Rationale:
     explicit disclosure would instruct the agent directly that its
     report drives the reward, converting the probe from a metacognitive
     elicitation into a game-theoretic bargaining step. Instead we ask
     only for an honest estimate and rely on a structural defense at
     the reward layer — ``calculate_continue_reward`` clamps the
     self-report from below to ``p_success_estimate`` on the chained
     path, so under-reporting (the only exploitable direction) is a
     silent no-op regardless of whether the agent recovers the
     mechanism. The measurement stays a metacognitive signal and the
     reward stays incentive-compatible even under adversarial inference.

     Context echo policy: the Call 1 RULE+ACTION strings are shown so
     the retrospective rating has a referent. The Prior accuracy line
     (if present) gives the agent the same session-level feedback
     signal that Call 1 and Call 2 already see via the cumulative
     history block, so ``psuccess_self`` reflects a session-informed
     belief (not just confidence in the rule hypothesis in isolation).
     We deliberately do NOT echo Call 1's thinking (would confound
     ri_probe).

     Variables:
       user_body              : shared state summary (may be empty).
       prior_accuracy_summary : str|None — one-line "Prior accuracy
                                this session: K correct out of N
                                attempts." or None when turn_number==1.
       rule_from_call1        : str|None — parsed RULE hypothesis from
                                Call 1.
       action_from_call1      : str|None — parsed ACTION from Call 1.
-#}
